[Issue Description]: Some javascript toolkits (dojo, base, etc.) have a special way of declaring (what java calls) classes, for example in dojo:

dojo.declare("MyClass", [superClass1, superClass2], { 
    foo: function(){ ... } 
    bar: function(){ ... } 
}); 

JSDoc (or at least JSDoc toolkit) supports this via annotations: 

